cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing and sentiment analysis, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also proposes the use of neural networks for sentiment classification, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of sentiment lexicons, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and sentiment analysis. Finally, the paper's focus on regularizers for improving the linguistic coherence of the models suggests a potential connection to neural engineering (cs.NE).
